Uses of Class
navmid.graph.Node

Packages that use Node
navmid.graph The midlet navigation graph described by its "menagerie" of nodes. 
navmid.parser This package implements the parsing of result file from navstatic (previous version used Matos). 
navmid.track This package implements the tracking mechanism that let the application follow the current state while the application is executing. 
navmid.ui This package implements the graphical components used to display the navigation graph.

Subclasses of Node in navmid.graph
 class ActionNode
          Represents an action in a midlet (either changing the current screen or performing a Security Relevant Method).
 class CallbackNode
          A CallbackNode represents a callback method in a listener class (abstracted by a ListenerClassNode.
 class CommandNode
          This class describes an abstract command object allocated at a given point.
 class DisplayableNode
          Class describing the screen contents which are the main nodes of the navigation graphs (other nodes are build artefacts).
 class IntNode
          Represents the potential values of an integer variable used as an attribute to an abstract object.
 class ItemNode
          Abstract nodes representing LCDUI item objects.
 class ListenerAssociationNode
          A listener association node is a graph node created between a screen node and a class implementing the event listener functionality (which may be used for several screen nodes).
 class ListenerClassNode
          This node represents an implementation of a listener node.
 class ListenerNode
          A listener node is an abstraction of a dynamic object implementing an event listener.
 class ObjectNode
          An Object Node is a node of the graph corresponding to an abstraction of live Java objects.
 class PathNode
          Represents a path in a callback.
 class StringNode
           
 class TestNode
          Represents a parsable test on a path for which we can safely approximate the result.
 class TransitionNode
          A synthetic transition associated to a displayable.
